docs.abstract: Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke has opened millions of acres of public lands for development while pursuing policies of protection in his home state.
docs.snippet: Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke has opened millions of acres of public lands for development while pursuing policies of protection in his home state.
docs.lead_paragraph: WHITEFISH, Mont. — When Interior Secretary Ryan Zinke was a state senator from this idyllic mountain town, he drove a Prius, sported a beard and pushed President Barack Obama to make clean energy a priority.

headline.main: Ryan Zinke Is Opening Up Public Lands. Just Not at Home.
headline.print_headline: Opening Public Lands to Oil and Gas. Just Not at Home.

docs.abstract: The rapper’s Twitter support of President Trump has been cheered by conservatives eager for a pop-culture champion.
docs.snippet: The rapper’s Twitter support of President Trump has been cheered by conservatives eager for a pop-culture champion.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the few days since the rapper Kanye West has doubled down on his public affinity for President Trump and other conservative figures on Twitter, his opinions — and the backlash they have wrought in some circles — have been hailed by those who have long seen the entertainment world as oppressively liberal.

headline.main: In Kanye West, the Right Sees Truth-Telling and a Rare A-List Ally
headline.print_headline: On the Right, Kanye West  Is Embraced As a Pop Ally

docs.abstract: In a private meeting, the owner of the Eagles called Mr. Trump’s tenure a “disastrous presidency,” using a vulgarity to emphasize “disastrous.”
docs.snippet: In a private meeting, the owner of the Eagles called Mr. Trump’s tenure a “disastrous presidency,” using a vulgarity to emphasize “disastrous.”
docs.lead_paragraph: Springtime in Washington usually brings the blooming of cherry blossom trees and a White House visit from the Super Bowl champions. Peak bloom happened weeks ago, but there’s still no sign of the Philadelphia Eagles, the N.F.L.’s current titleholders.

headline.main: When — if Ever — Will the Super Bowl Champion Eagles Visit the White House?

docs.abstract: Even when ‘Scandal’ veered into the absurd, I never gave up on its heroine.
docs.snippet: Even when ‘Scandal’ veered into the absurd, I never gave up on its heroine.
docs.lead_paragraph: Years before Hillary Clinton accepted the Democratic nomination for president in a suffragette-inspired white pantsuit, Olivia Pope had been running Washington in her tailored armor. And I, like millions of American women, have been a proud member of her Gladiator Nation since “Scandal” premiered on ABC in 2012.

docs.abstract: Buck and Boogz are idealists who want to bring dance to new audiences. Their stage show, “Love Heals All Wounds,” takes on contemporary social ills.
docs.snippet: Buck and Boogz are idealists who want to bring dance to new audiences. Their stage show, “Love Heals All Wounds,” takes on contemporary social ills.
docs.lead_paragraph: The dancers Lil Buck and Jon Boogz — Buck and Boogz for short — share a mission: nothing less than to improve the world through dance. Both emerged from the street-dance scenes in their hometowns, Memphis (Buck) and Miami (Boogz). They met at an open jam session at the Debbie Reynolds Dance Studio in Los Angeles almost 10 years ago. As they put it, they recognized each other’s skills but also connected on a higher plane, as two idealists who believe that dance can bring people closer and perhaps even change the way they think.

headline.main: Lil Buck and Jon Boogz, Dancing to Improve the World
headline.print_headline: 2 Idealists, Tackling Social Ills With Street Moves
